   386→                        <div id="content">Let $f(n)$ be minimal such that every triangle-free graph $G$ with $n$ vertices and diameter $2$ contains a vertex with degree $\geq f(n)$. <br><br>What is the order of growth of $f(n)$? Does $f(n)/\sqrt{n}\to \infty$? </div>
